1
00:00:13,931 --> 00:00:16,308
从很久以前开始
In Sixteen Hundred Seven

2
00:00:16,475 --> 00:00:19,102
航海是我本事
We sailed the open sea

3
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:21,438
荣耀尊贵财富全靠
For glory, God and gold

4
00:00:21,605 --> 00:00:24,650
维吉尼亚大公司
And the Virginia Company

5
00:00:24,816 --> 00:00:27,402
新的世界就像天堂
For the New World is like heaven

6
00:00:27,569 --> 00:00:30,197
我们大家都向往
And we'll all be rich and free

7
00:00:30,364 --> 00:00:32,449
要消息灵通全靠这
Or so we have been told

8
00:00:32,616 --> 00:00:35,786
维吉尼亚大公司
By the Virginia Company

9
00:00:35,953 --> 00:00:37,955
消息灵通全靠这
So we have been told

10
00:00:38,121 --> 00:00:41,542
维吉尼亚大公司
By the Virginia Company

11
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:53,971
荣耀尊贵财富全靠
For glory, God, and gold

12
00:00:54,137 --> 00:00:57,224
维吉尼亚大公司
And the Virginia Company

13
00:00:58,267 --> 00:01:00,060
-  准备好吊起大跑了吗？ -  准备好了！
- Ready to hoist the cannon? - Aye!

14
00:01:00,227 --> 00:01:01,770
你看  那是庄迈斯吗？
Hey, look. Is that Smith?

15
00:01:01,937 --> 00:01:04,022
是他  没错  老练的水手
That's him, all right. The old sea dog.

16
00:01:04,189 --> 00:01:07,234
庄迈斯上尉 我听说过不少他的传奇
Captain John Smith? I've heard amazing stories about him.

17
00:01:07,401 --> 00:01:09,403
你要跟我们一块去远航吗？
Are you coming on this voyage, too?

18
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:13,573
当然了  那还用说吗？ 打印第安鬼哪能没有他啊
Course he is, you half-wit! You can't fight Indians without John Smith!

19
00:01:13,740 --> 00:01:17,578
就是嘛 这种场面怎么能丢下我呢
That's right. I'm not about to let you boys have all the fun.

20
00:01:18,662 --> 00:01:21,039
我们靠岸的那地方
On the beaches of Virginny

21
00:01:21,206 --> 00:01:23,834
满地都是宝藏
There's diamonds like debris

22
00:01:24,001 --> 00:01:26,545
它遍地黄金
There's silver rivers flowin'

23
00:01:26,712 --> 00:01:29,590
不用愁口袋会响叮
Gold you pick right off a tree

24
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:31,675
这金块给我的爱人
With a nugget for my Winnie

25
00:01:31,842 --> 00:01:34,553
这一块给我自己
And another one for me

26
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:36,680
其它所得通通交给
And all the rest'll go

27
00:01:36,847 --> 00:01:40,058
维吉尼亚大公司
To the Virginia Company

28
00:01:40,225 --> 00:01:42,686
荣耀尊贵财富全靠
It's glory, God, and gold

29
00:01:42,853 --> 00:01:48,191
维吉尼亚大公司
And the Virginia Company

30
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:56,408
抓紧缆绳
Full anchor release!

31
00:01:56,575 --> 00:01:58,076
小心  小心
Come on, lads! Come on!

32
00:01:58,243 --> 00:02:00,078
抓紧缆绳
Give me a hand, someone!

33
00:02:00,245 --> 00:02:01,455
用力
Watch out!

34
00:02:05,584 --> 00:02:07,878
快受不了这个暴雨
Faster! She's taking on more water!

35
00:02:11,757 --> 00:02:13,592
小心
Look out!

36
00:02:17,262 --> 00:02:19,681
迈斯  快下来呀
John! Get down here!

37
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:22,142
这门跑快散掉了
The cannons are breaking loose!

38
00:02:26,229 --> 00:02:27,856
-抓方向盘！ -是的  大人！
- Reef the topsails! - Aye, sir!

39
00:02:28,023 --> 00:02:29,649
大家不要慌！
Steady on your course!

40
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:32,527
镇定点  汤姆斯 先把船稳住
It's all right, Thomas! We'll get her tied off.

41
00:02:32,694 --> 00:02:33,987
大伙  祈祷吧
Say your prayers, lads!

42
00:02:40,202 --> 00:02:42,913
小心！
Look out!

43
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:44,873
汤姆斯  小心！
Thomas, watch out...!

44
00:02:49,378 --> 00:02:50,837
救命啊！
Help!

45
00:02:51,546 --> 00:02:53,298
有人落海了
Man overboard!

46
00:02:53,465 --> 00:02:54,466
救命啊！
Help!

47
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:56,551
别下去  他死定了
Stay your course! He's lost!

48
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:57,719
救命啊！
Help!

49
00:02:57,886 --> 00:03:00,597
拽绳子 遵命  大人！
- Pull the pin. - Aye, sir!

50
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:05,769
迈斯
Smith!

51
00:03:06,937 --> 00:03:08,063
迈斯

52
00:03:09,523 --> 00:03:11,483
你疯了你
Are you crazy?

53
00:03:13,110 --> 00:03:15,612
撑下去  汤姆斯  我帮你
Hang on, Thomas. I've got you!

54
00:03:18,073 --> 00:03:20,158
快  绳子！
Quick... the rope!

55
00:03:20,951 --> 00:03:22,911
拉起来
Heave!

56
00:03:27,749 --> 00:03:29,793
伙伴们  拉啊
Come on, lads! Pull!

57
00:03:32,421 --> 00:03:34,381
拉  用力拉
Pull! Pull!

58
00:03:34,548 --> 00:03:36,133
大伙用全力
Put your back into it!

59
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:39,302
拉…
Pull! Pull!

60
00:03:39,469 --> 00:03:41,138
坚持住
Hang on!

61
00:03:43,515 --> 00:03:45,976
好  把他救回来了
Ah, my lucky lad!

62
00:03:46,643 --> 00:03:49,646
真够呛
Well, that was refreshing.

63
00:03:49,813 --> 00:03:52,816
多亏有你呀  迈斯 哪里
- Well done, Smith. - Of course...

64
00:03:52,983 --> 00:03:54,609
是大伙一起出力的
...you'd all do the same for me.

65
00:03:55,569 --> 00:03:56,736
是  是 就是嘛
- Yes, yes. - Sure, sure.

66
00:03:56,903 --> 00:03:59,281
-我们都出力了  ！ -对  我们都出力了
- Of course we would! Absolutely! - Yeah, we would.

67
00:04:01,324 --> 00:04:03,160
出事了吗？
Trouble on deck?

68
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:06,163
雷利夫总督大人 汤姆斯掉进海里了
- Governor Ratcliffe! - Thomas fell overboard, sir.

69
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:08,540
能把他救回来 真是感谢上帝
Thank heavens he's been successfully retrieved.

70
00:04:08,707 --> 00:04:10,834
记你一功  迈斯 谢谢  大人
- Well done, Smith. - Thank you, sir.

71
00:04:11,001 --> 00:04:15,172
别再大意了 不多久我们就到达新大陆
Don't lose heart, men. It won't be long before we reach the New World,

72
00:04:15,338 --> 00:04:18,675
知道什么在等着我们吗？
and remember what awaits us there...

73
00:04:18,842 --> 00:04:23,930
自由  锦绣前程 多彩多姿的生活
Freedom, prosperity, the adventure of our lives.

74
00:04:24,097 --> 00:04:26,516
你们全都是来自英国 最优秀的队员
You're the finest crew England has to offer,

75
00:04:26,683 --> 00:04:28,935
无论什么  不管是风是雨
and nothing, not wind nor rain,

76
00:04:29,102 --> 00:04:32,689
还是上千万个蛮夷部族 都要勇往直前
nor a thousand bloodthirsty savages shall stand in our way.

77
00:04:32,856 --> 00:04:34,566
坚持下去
Carry on, men!

78
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:38,487
真是振奋人心啊  大人
A stirring oration, sir.

79
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:41,406
现在大伙热血沸腾
I'm sure the men were most exhilarated!

80
00:04:41,573 --> 00:04:47,579
但愿如此  我还得靠这些 愚蠢的人帮我挖金子呢  对吧？
Let us hope so. I'll need those witless peasants to dig up my gold, won't I?

81
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:52,042
哇  这新大陆可真不赖  迈斯
This New World's going to be great, John.

82
00:04:52,209 --> 00:04:53,919
让我捧着大量黄金
I'm going to get a pile of gold,

83
00:04:54,085 --> 00:04:58,507
回家盖大楼  要是蛮夷他们 敢来捣乱的话  我就给他一枪
build me a big house, and if any Indian tries to stop me, I'll blast him.

84
00:04:58,673 --> 00:05:01,176
你尽管去照顾你的黄金 汤姆斯
Just worry about that fortune of yours, Thomas.

85
00:05:01,343 --> 00:05:04,346
蛮夷交给我就行了 你是说蛮夷很难对付？
- Leave the savages to me. - You think they'll give us trouble?

86
00:05:04,513 --> 00:05:07,474
庄迈斯会让他们吃苦头
Not as much trouble as Smith'll give them.

87
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:09,893
来一个我们就杀一个
We'll kill ourselves an injun

88
00:05:10,060 --> 00:05:12,729
来两个…
Or maybe two or three

89
00:05:12,896 --> 00:05:17,943
我忠心耿耿属於这 维吉尼亚大公司
We're stalwart men and bold ofthe Virginia Company

90
00:05:18,109 --> 00:05:20,612
你觉得新大陆会是什么样子的呢？
What do you suppose the New World will look like?

91
00:05:20,779 --> 00:05:22,572
我觉得跟其他地方没什么两样
Like all the others, I suppose.

92
00:05:22,739 --> 00:05:25,784
新大陆我以前见过不少了 汤姆斯
I've seen hundreds of New Worlds, Thomas.

93
00:05:25,951 --> 00:05:28,578
这个又能有什么不同？
What could possibly be different about this one?

94
00:05:29,663 --> 00:05:30,830
荣耀尊贵财富全靠
It's glory

95
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:37,003
维吉尼亚大公司
God, and gold

96
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:37,002
And the Virginia Company

97
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:49,558
「风中奇缘」

98
00:06:16,918 --> 00:06:19,129
打着鼓来敲着钟
Steady as the beating drum

99
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:21,631
歌唱不停庆丰收
Singing to the cedar flute

100
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:23,883
春去秋来冬又过
Seasons go and seasons come

101
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:28,221
收获载满一篓筐
Bring the corn and bear the fruit

102
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:30,307
靠着河边水又清
By the waters sweet and clean

103
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:32,726
万物一起来和应
Where the mighty sturgeon lives

104
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:35,228
食物水果洒满地
Plant the squash and reap the bean

105
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:39,316
天生天养乐无比
All the earth our Mother gives

106
00:06:39,482 --> 00:06:41,735
悠哉悠哉歌声中
O, Great Spirit, hear our song

107
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:44,029
天生天养乐无比
Help us keep the ancient ways

108
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:46,948
围着火来胆更壮
Keep the sacred fires strong

109
00:06:47,115 --> 00:06:50,577
日子一天又一天
Walk in balance all our days

110
00:06:50,744 --> 00:06:52,829
春去秋来冬又过
Seasons go and seasons come

111
00:06:52,996 --> 00:06:55,332
打着鼓来敲着钟
Steady as the beating drum

112
00:06:55,498 --> 00:07:01,338
每当收获不放弃
Plum to seed to bud to plum

113
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:06,760
打着鼓来敲着钟
Steady as the beating drum

114
00:07:17,437 --> 00:07:20,649
包华顿 纪克泰

115
00:07:20,899 --> 00:07:22,984
回到家来真好
It's good to be home.

116
00:07:25,362 --> 00:07:27,530
木索乌美族被打败了
The Massawomecks are defeated!

117
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:32,202
靠兄弟们同心协力 我们的部族又太平了
With the help of our brothers, our villages are safe again.

118
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:37,874
看你胜利归来令族人多兴奋哪
Your return has brought much joy to the village.

119
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:40,460
他们都笑得多开心
Look at all the smiling faces.

120
00:07:41,336 --> 00:07:44,964
是啊！不过好像还少了一个人
Yes. But there's one smiling face I don't see.

121
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:46,257
我女儿呢？
Where is my daughter?

122
00:07:46,424 --> 00:07:48,134
你是说宝嘉康蒂啊
You know Pocahontas.

123
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:50,178
她有她母亲的遗传
She has her mother's spirit.

124
00:07:50,345 --> 00:07:53,431
永远随着风向到处跑
She goes wherever the wind takes her.

125
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:13,535
宝嘉康蒂！
Pocahontas!

126
00:08:14,786 --> 00:08:16,413
你爸爸回来了
Your father's back.

127
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:18,206
快下来
Come down here!

128
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,291
爸回来了  菲莉
He's back, Flit.

129
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:26,214
走吧  米糕
Come on, Meeko!

130
00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:36,474
不  又来了
No! Not that... way.

131
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:47,027
爱现
Show-off.

132
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:03,001
宝嘉康蒂？
Pocahontas?

133
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:06,963
宝嘉康蒂？你没事吧？
Pocahontas? Are you all right?

134
00:09:07,756 --> 00:09:11,092
你不要再装神弄鬼了 我可不会跟你跳到水里去的
You'd better be all right, because I'm not coming in after you...

135
00:09:14,971 --> 00:09:18,475
就爱玩这种花样 你以为我们还小啊？
Don't you think we're getting a little old for these games?

136
00:09:38,495 --> 00:09:40,497
帮忙翻过来
Help me turn this thing over.

137
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,043
你刚刚在上面干什么？
What were you doing up there?

138
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:48,088
思考啊  米糕
Thinking. Meeko!

139
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:51,216
又在想那个梦啊 那你又想到什么呢？
About the dream again? Have you figured it out yet?

140
00:09:51,382 --> 00:09:54,052
其中一定有什么含意 我就是搞不懂
I know it means something, I just don't know what.

141
00:09:54,219 --> 00:09:57,597
你应该去问问你爸爸 说得也是
- You should ask your father about it. - Maybe I should.

142
00:09:58,056 --> 00:09:59,557
来吧  菲莉
Come on, Flit.

143
00:10:00,350 --> 00:10:02,852
不要再疯了  我们该走了
Quit playing around. We have to get back.

144
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:08,525
就跟敌人决一死战
...faced a determined enemy.

145
00:10:08,691 --> 00:10:11,444
那场仗打从太阳升起开始
The battle lasted from the rising of the sun

146
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,863
一直激战到夜幕低垂
until the evening shadows fell.

147
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:18,868
勇士们都奋勇杀敌 可就数高刚最英勇
Our warriors fought with courage, but none as bravely as Kocoum,

148
00:10:19,035 --> 00:10:21,871
他就像猛虎出闸 所向匹敌
for he attacked with the fierce strength of the bear.

149
00:10:22,038 --> 00:10:25,333
-他智勇双全  证明他是… -你看  高刚真的好帅哦
- He has proven himself to be... - He is so handsome!

150
00:10:26,209 --> 00:10:27,710
他的笑容才迷人呢
I especially love the smile.

151
00:10:27,877 --> 00:10:29,754
把敌人彻底歼灭
...destroying every enemy in his path.

152
00:10:29,921 --> 00:10:32,507
今晚我们要为他庆祝
Tonight, we will feast in his honor.

153
00:10:36,845 --> 00:10:38,805
乖女儿 爸
- My daughter. - Winggapo, Father.

154
00:10:38,972 --> 00:10:41,516
看到你我就高兴了
Seeing you gives me greatjoy.

155
00:10:41,683 --> 00:10:44,310
你能够平安回来 真是太好了
I'm so glad you've come home safely.

156
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:47,438
跟我来  我们要好好谈谈
Come with me. We have much to talk about.

157
00:10:47,605 --> 00:10:50,149
我不在的时候 你都做了些什么？
I want to hear everything you've been doing.

158
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:58,700
爸  好多个晚上 我都在做同一个怪梦
Father, for many nights now, I've been having a very strange dream.

159
00:10:58,867 --> 00:11:02,412
我想它是要告诉我 有一些兴奋的事将要发生了
It's telling me something's about to happen, something exciting.

160
00:11:02,579 --> 00:11:05,915
没错 是有些兴奋的事情要发生了
Yes. Something exciting is about to happen.

161
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:08,209
真的  是什么？
Really? What is it?

162
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:11,921
高刚已经跟我开口向你提亲了
Kocoum has asked to seek your hand in marriage.

163
00:11:12,088 --> 00:11:13,673
要嫁给高刚？
Marry Kocoum?

164
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:18,970
我告诉他  我是求之不得
I told him it would make my heart soar.

165
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:25,977
可是…他好古板哦
But he's so... serious.

166
00:11:26,144 --> 00:11:29,105
乖女儿  高刚会是个好丈夫的
My daughter, Kocoum will make a fine husband.

167
00:11:29,272 --> 00:11:33,067
他为人忠诚  坚强 绝对是个可托付终身的对象
He is loyal and strong and will build you a good house with sturdy walls.

168
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:35,653
嫁给他  你会很幸福的
With him, you will be safe from harm.

169
00:11:35,820 --> 00:11:38,615
爸  我想我的梦 是在指示我另外一条路
Father, I think my dream is pointing me down another path.

170
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:40,325
这就是你要走的路啊
This is the right path for you.

171
00:11:40,491 --> 00:11:42,327
我就不能选择吗？
But why can't I choose...

172
00:11:50,460 --> 00:11:53,213
宝嘉康蒂  听我说
Pocahontas, come with me.

173
00:11:53,379 --> 00:11:55,048
你身为酋长的女儿
You are the daughter of the chief.

174
00:11:55,214 --> 00:11:57,634
是时候要建立在族人中的地位
It is time to take your place among our people.

175
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:02,388
就算是树高千丈 终究要落叶归根
Even the wild mountain stream must someday join the big river.

176
00:12:02,555 --> 00:12:06,267
看着河水流过它
As the river cuts his path

177
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:10,521
黑夜强风也不怕
Though the river's proud and strong

178
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:15,193
弯弯曲曲任由它
He will choose the smoothest course

179
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:19,697
总有一天会到家
That's why rivers live so long.

180
00:12:20,031 --> 00:12:22,575
它坚强
They're steady

181
00:12:22,742 --> 00:12:26,871
不怕风吹和雨打
As the steady beating drum

182
00:12:27,038 --> 00:12:30,041
这项链是你妈妈的嫁妆
Your mother wore this for our wedding.

183
00:12:30,208 --> 00:12:33,503
她老盼望能看你戴着它出嫁
It was her dream to see you wear it at your own.

184
00:12:35,797 --> 00:12:37,757
真配你
It suits you.

185
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:43,888
他要我稳定下来
He wants me to be steady.

186
00:12:45,056 --> 00:12:46,516
落叶归根
Like the river.

187
00:12:50,353 --> 00:12:52,689
可是我要长流不息
But it's not steady at all.

188
00:12:55,024 --> 00:12:57,360
滚滚的河水是我所爱
What I love most about rivers is

189
00:12:57,527 --> 00:12:59,445
它不停地向两岸拍
You can't step in the same river twice

190
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:01,739
它日夜不停流过逍遥自在
The water's always changing

191
00:13:01,906 --> 00:13:03,616
它勇往直前  没有终点
Always flowing

192
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:05,535
努力付出代价
But people, I guess can't live like that

193
00:13:05,702 --> 00:13:07,287
人们不停忙碌
We all must pay a price

194
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:10,957
可曾仔细想过
To be safe we lose our chance of ever knowing

195
00:13:11,124 --> 00:13:14,877
流水弯弯哪里载
What's around the river bend

196
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:17,755
看着滚滚流水两岸拍
Waiting just around the river bend

197
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:20,383
仔细看着
I look once more

198
00:13:20,550 --> 00:13:22,302
滚滚流水两岸拍
Just around the river bend

199
00:13:22,468 --> 00:13:24,053
永不停息
Beyond the shore

200
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:25,763
看海鸥畅飞
Where the gulls fly free

201
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:27,890
飞往何方？
Don't know what for

202
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:30,101
可曾留下仔细看
What I dream the day might send

203
00:13:30,268 --> 00:13:33,354
滚滚流水两岸拍
Just around the river bend

204
00:13:33,521 --> 00:13:36,607
无尽
For me

205
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:41,195
永无止境
Coming for me

206
00:13:41,362 --> 00:13:45,992
我无时无刻感觉到它 这里就是我的家
I feel it there beyond those trees Or right behind these waterfalls

207
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:49,495
它不停伴着鼓的敲打声音
Can I ignore that sound of distant drumming?

208
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:53,416
看那滚滚流水流往何方 你可曾想过
For a handsome, sturdy husband who builds handsome, sturdy walls

209
00:13:53,583 --> 00:13:57,420
它暗示有些事情将会发生
And never dreams that something might be coming

210
00:13:57,587 --> 00:14:01,215
滚滚流水两岸拍
Just around the river bend

211
00:14:01,382 --> 00:14:04,927
流往何处不必猜

212
00:14:05,094 --> 00:14:07,013
不眠不休
I look once more

213
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:08,681
滚滚流水两岸拍
Just around the river bend

214
00:14:08,848 --> 00:14:10,600
永不停息
Beyond the shore

215
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:12,351
永远不停息
Somewhere past the sea

216
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:14,437
心在何方
Don't know what for

217
00:14:14,604 --> 00:14:16,397
我的美梦向天飞
Why do all my dreams extend

218
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:20,276
滚滚流水两岸拍
Just around the river bend?

219
00:14:20,443 --> 00:14:23,780
滚滚流水两岸拍
Just around the river bend

220
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:29,577
我该选择些什么
Should I choose the smoothest course

221
00:14:29,744 --> 00:14:33,498
越想越会心事多
Steady as the beating drum?

222
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:37,627
如果我要嫁给他
Should I marry Kocoum?

223
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:42,548
一生梦想彷佛不再
Is all my dreaming at an end?

224
00:14:44,759 --> 00:14:48,471
心在彷徨
Or do you still

225
00:14:48,638 --> 00:14:53,893
该往何方看着
Wait for me, dream giver?

226
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:59,941
滚滚流水
Just around the river

227
00:15:01,275 --> 00:15:05,446
两岸拍
Bend

228
00:15:31,389 --> 00:15:33,558
是不是宝嘉康蒂呀？
Is that my Pocahontas?

229
00:15:34,934 --> 00:15:37,687
柳树婆婆  我有话要跟你说
Grandmother Willow, I need to talk to you.

230
00:15:39,689 --> 00:15:42,150
你早啊  我的孩子
Good morning, child.

231
00:15:42,316 --> 00:15:44,819
我就是盼着你今天能来
I was hoping you'd visit today.

232
00:15:45,695 --> 00:15:48,114
那是你妈妈的项链吧
Why, your mother's necklace!

233
00:15:48,281 --> 00:15:50,825
我就是要来跟你说这个的
That's what I wanted to talk to you about.

234
00:15:50,992 --> 00:15:53,077
我爸爸想要我嫁给高刚
My father wants me to marry Kocoum.

235
00:15:53,244 --> 00:15:56,664
高刚？可是他好古板
Kocoum? But he's so serious!

236
00:15:56,831 --> 00:16:00,543
就是嘛 可是爸爸认为这就是我的路
I know. My father thinks it's the right path for me.

237
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:03,671
但是…我老做一个梦 这个梦…
But lately, I've been having this dream, and I think it's...

238
00:16:03,838 --> 00:16:08,217
噢  一个梦啊 那就赶快说出来听听啊
Oh, a dream! Let's hear all about it!

239
00:16:09,844 --> 00:16:11,345
别吵
Quiet!

240
00:16:12,889 --> 00:16:14,098
别吵

241
00:16:20,021 --> 00:16:22,064
孩子  刚才你在说…
Now, child, you were saying?

242
00:16:22,231 --> 00:16:24,734
我跑着穿过树林
Well, I'm running through the woods,

243
00:16:24,901 --> 00:16:27,528
然后就在我面前有一支箭
and then right there in front of me is an arrow.

244
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:30,072
当我望向它  它就开始转动
As I look at it, it starts to spin.

245
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:33,826
一支转动的箭？那多不寻常啊
A spinning arrow? How unusual!

246
00:16:33,993 --> 00:16:39,373
对  它不停地转  越转越快 越转越快  可是突然间  它停了
Yes, it spins faster and faster and faster... until, suddenly, it stops.

247
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:48,591
看来这转动的箭 似乎是在指引你往下要走的路
Well, it seems to me this spinning arrow is pointing you down your path.

248
00:16:48,925 --> 00:16:51,886
可是柳树婆婆  是什么路啊？
But, Grandmother Willow, what is my path?

249
00:16:52,053 --> 00:16:53,721
我要怎么样才能找到它呢？
How am I ever going to find it?

250
00:16:54,931 --> 00:16:58,434
你妈妈也曾经问过我 同一个问题
Your mother asked me the very same question.

251
00:16:58,601 --> 00:17:00,853
真的？那你怎么说的？
She did? What did you tell her?

252
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:03,856
我就叫她仔细听
I told her to listen.

253
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:06,859
在你的周围都是些神灵  孩子
All around you are spirits, child.

254
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:11,948
生活在土里  流水中  天空上
They live in the earth, the water, the sky.

255
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:16,035
只要细听就有指引
If you listen, they will guide you.

256
00:17:19,205 --> 00:17:21,666
-我听见风 -对了
- I hear the wind. - Yes.

257
00:17:21,832 --> 00:17:24,085
它在说些什么？
What is it telling you?

258
00:17:24,252 --> 00:17:26,337
我听不太懂
I don't understand.

259
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:33,427
你会明白
You will understand

260
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:36,973
用心来聆听
Listen with your heart

261
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:40,559
心灵的声音
You will understand

262
00:17:41,143 --> 00:17:47,149
让声音轻轻地告诉你人生真谛
Let it break upon you like a wave upon the sand

263
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:49,151
它在说有些什么要来
It's saying something's coming.

264
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:50,903
一团怪云？
Strange clouds?

265
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:54,282
用心来聆听
Listen with your heart

266
00:17:54,448 --> 00:17:58,369
心灵的声音
You will understand

267
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:06,669
看见什么了？
What do you see?

268
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:11,382
云彩  一团怪云
Clouds. Strange clouds.

269
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:20,182
你看  华根 整个新大陆遍布黄金
Look at it, Wiggins, an entire New World chock-full of gold,

270
00:18:20,349 --> 00:18:22,351
在等着我
Just waiting for me.

271
00:18:22,518 --> 00:18:26,647
有更新鲜刺激的事 在等着我们呢  对吗？波斯
And scores of adventures waiting for us, right, Percy?

272
00:18:26,814 --> 00:18:28,607
你说我们会碰上蛮夷吗？
Do you think we'll meet some savages?

273
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:31,694
真碰上 我们就好好地跟他打个招呼
Ifwe do, we shall be sure to give them a proper English greeting.

274
00:18:31,861 --> 00:18:33,654
见面礼
Gift baskets!

275
00:18:35,197 --> 00:18:37,366
难怪人们喜欢他不喜欢我
And he came so highly recommended.

276
00:18:40,161 --> 00:18:43,706
太理想了  大人  海水深度正好 我们可以直接靠岸了
It's perfect, the water's deep enough. We can pull right up to shore.

277
00:18:43,873 --> 00:18:45,374
嘿  那里  波斯
Hey, there, Percy.

278
00:18:47,084 --> 00:18:49,378
好极了  船立刻靠岸 都安排好了  大人
- Very well, then. Give the order. - Already done, sir.

279
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:51,547
只等大人下令 随时可以出发了
I've got a crew assembled, and they're ready to go.

280
00:18:51,714 --> 00:18:53,424
那些土著嘛
About the natives...

281
00:18:53,591 --> 00:18:56,010
就看你的 千万别让那些蛮夷
I'm counting on you to make sure those filthy heathens

282
00:18:56,177 --> 00:18:57,678
来坏我们的大事
don't disrupt our mission.

283
00:18:57,845 --> 00:19:00,639
如果他们跟我以前 对付过的蛮夷一样的话
Well, if they're anything like the savages I've fought before,

284
00:19:00,806 --> 00:19:02,141
那绝对没问题
it's nothing I can't handle.

285
00:19:02,308 --> 00:19:05,311
好啊！那就没什么可担心的  迈斯
Right. That'll be all, Smith. There's a good man.

286
00:19:05,478 --> 00:19:07,229
再见  波斯
See ya, Percy.

287
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:11,942
人们就是喜欢他
The men like Smith, don't they?

288
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:18,240
可我从来就不受欢迎 你有我呀
- I've never been a popular man. - I like you.

289
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:22,244
别以为我不知道那些人 在背后是怎么说我的
Don't think I don't know what those backstabbers at court say about me.

290
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:24,872
噢  对  都说您是个老拼命往上爬
Oh, yes, all that talk about being a pathetic social climber

291
00:19:25,039 --> 00:19:27,541
可是却一事无成的可怜虫 我很清楚
- who's failed at everything... - I'm very well aware that this is

292
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:31,087
这次是我翻身的机会 你等着瞧  华根
my last chance for glory. But mark my words, Wiggins,

293
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:33,923
当詹姆国王看到那成堆的黄金
when King James sees the gold these peasants unearth,

294
00:19:34,090 --> 00:19:37,760
这最后的胜利就是我的了
success will be mine, at last.

295
00:19:39,762 --> 00:19:41,889
醒醒！伸个懒腰！ 在桁端的两个！
- Wake up! Shake a leg! - Two of you up on the yardarm!

296
00:19:42,056 --> 00:19:43,557
简直是难以置信
It's incredible.

297
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:47,061
全都是我们的？ 我从来没见过这么好的地方
And it's all ours. I've never seen anything like it.

298
00:19:47,228 --> 00:19:49,355
其实这个地方 像雷利夫的内裤  我也不在乎
It can look like Ratcliffe's knickers for all I care,

299
00:19:49,522 --> 00:19:52,316
只要能离开这艘烂船
Just as long as I get off this stinking boat!

300
00:19:52,483 --> 00:19:55,444
好了  兄弟们  我们老远地 跑来别站着看
Come on, men. We didn't come all this way just to look at it.

301
00:20:50,583 --> 00:20:54,879
下船吧  伙伴们 用力  用劲  拉紧啊
Keep it taut, lads. Keep it taut! Steady! Steady!

302
00:20:55,045 --> 00:20:56,756
抓牢  抓牢
Hold up! That's far enough!

303
00:20:56,922 --> 00:20:59,258
就这样  绑牢它
All right now... tie her off!

304
00:20:59,425 --> 00:21:01,093
庄哥  抓到这头
Here, John, tie off this end.

305
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:03,804
庄哥  庄哥？
John? John?

306
00:21:05,014 --> 00:21:07,975
你爬上去干什么啊？ 想看清楚点
- What are you doing up there? - Getting a better look.

307
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:34,585
嘿！
Hey!

308
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:43,802
小东西  你样子长得很奇怪
Well... you're a strange looking fellow.

309
00:21:43,969 --> 00:21:45,471
你饿了吗？
You hungry?

310
00:21:45,638 --> 00:21:47,890
拿去吧  这是饼乾
Here you go. It's a biscuit.

311
00:21:48,057 --> 00:21:50,684
食物  对！可以吃的哦
It's food. Well, sort of.

312
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:54,396
你喜欢啊
You like it, eh?

313
00:21:54,563 --> 00:21:57,358
连吃四个月你就会知道了
Well, try eating it for four months straight.

314
00:22:01,821 --> 00:22:03,906
你伙伴在后头啊
You got a friend back there?

315
00:22:13,999 --> 00:22:17,044
嘿  什么？小心
Hey... what the... What...? Watch out.

316
00:22:18,921 --> 00:22:22,591
别过来  小心！ 庄哥  快点下来！
- No... get that... Look out! - John, you better get down here!

317
00:22:22,758 --> 00:22:26,595
总督大人要上岸了 好了  ！  改天再跟你玩  再见
- The governor's coming ashore. - All right. I'm leaving.

318
00:22:43,571 --> 00:22:44,738
看到他们的皮肤吗？
Did you see their skin?

319
00:22:44,905 --> 00:22:45,906
苍白  带病态
Pale and sickly.

320
00:22:46,073 --> 00:22:47,449
他们脸上有毛  和狗一样
They have hair on their faces like dogs.

321
00:22:47,616 --> 00:22:51,787
兄弟们 要先弄清楚他们的来路
My brothers, we must know more about these visitors.

322
00:22:51,954 --> 00:22:54,957
纪克泰  看到什么了？
Kekata, what do you see?

323
00:23:11,473 --> 00:23:13,809
他们非我族人
These are not men like us...

324
00:23:14,685 --> 00:23:19,565
全是一些受体罚的怪兽
...but strange beasts with bodies that shine like the sun,

325
00:23:19,732 --> 00:23:23,861
携带着会发出雷火的武器
and weapons that spout fire and thunder.

326
00:23:27,865 --> 00:23:31,493
他们像群恶狼四处徘徊
They prowl the earth like ravenous wolves,

327
00:23:31,660 --> 00:23:34,913
不停在寻找捕食的猎物
consuming everything in their path.

328
00:23:39,543 --> 00:23:43,297
包华顿酋长 我这就带着族中勇士沿河道突击
Great Powhatan, I will lead our warriors to the river and attack.

329
00:23:43,464 --> 00:23:47,343
杀他个措手不及 就像打败木索乌美族一样
We will destroy these invaders the way we destroyed the Massawomecks.

330
00:23:47,509 --> 00:23:50,846
高刚  在那场仗中 我们对敌人了若指掌
Kocoum, in that battle we knew how to fight our enemy,

331
00:23:51,013 --> 00:23:53,432
可是我们对这群来客 却一无所知
but these pale visitors are strange to us.

332
00:23:53,599 --> 00:23:55,976
带些人去沿河道监视他们
Take some men to the river to observe them.

333
00:23:56,143 --> 00:23:58,687
希望他们不过是路过而已
Let us hope they do not intend to stay.

334
00:24:00,022 --> 00:24:03,651
我在此宣布 此地一切资源
I hereby claim this land and all its riches

335
00:24:03,817 --> 00:24:06,111
尽归詹姆国王陛下所拥有
in the name of His Majesty, King James the First,

336
00:24:06,278 --> 00:24:10,616
同时将此地命名为詹姆镇
and do so name this settlement Jamestown.

337
00:24:10,783 --> 00:24:14,745
精彩  精彩 大人说得太精彩了
Bravo! Bravo! Beautifully spoken, sir!

338
00:24:14,912 --> 00:24:16,205
快来  波斯
Hurry now, Percy.

339
00:24:16,372 --> 00:24:18,791
快些弄干净见见新大陆了
We must be all squeaky clean for the New World.

340
00:25:01,917 --> 00:25:05,838
庄上尉  看来我选的这个地方 再理想不过了
Captain Smith, it appears I've selected the perfect location.

341
00:25:06,005 --> 00:25:07,214
看不见有蛮夷
Not a savage in sight.

342
00:25:07,381 --> 00:25:10,092
只是我们没看到 不等于他们不存在
Just because we don't see them doesn't mean they're not out there.

343
00:25:10,926 --> 00:25:15,723
也许你该去打探看看 他们究竟躲在何处
Then perhaps you should venture forth and determine their whereabouts.

344
00:25:16,432 --> 00:25:18,892
如果真有蛮夷的话 包在我身上
If there are any Indians out there, I'll find them.

345
00:25:21,979 --> 00:25:23,647
好了  朋友们  开工了
Now, gentlemen, to work.

346
00:25:23,814 --> 00:25:26,525
你们去负责装卸 你们建跑垒
You men, get the ship unloaded, you men build the fort.

347
00:25:26,692 --> 00:25:29,445
剩下的人拿圆锹出来
The rest of you... break out the shovels!

348
00:25:29,737 --> 00:25:32,489
立刻开始挖地 挖地？
- It's time to start digging! - Digging?

349
00:25:32,656 --> 00:25:35,743
当然了  别忘了那些西班牙人
Well, of course! Let's not forget what the Spanish found

350
00:25:36,034 --> 00:25:38,036
在这儿找到了些什么
when they came to the New World.

351
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:41,081
黄金！  满山都是
Gold! Mountains of it.

352
00:25:41,248 --> 00:25:44,793
多年来  这里的宝贵资源
